<dl id="n19084d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n19" href="#n19084d">N19 (VI.B.19)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n19all.htm#n19084d"> 84(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bowel joins in / conversation</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">I then had the satisfaction of seeing <font color="green">[the wolf man&apos;s]</font> doubt dwindle away, as in the course of the work his bowel began, like a hysterically affected organ, to &lsquo;join in the conversation&rsquo;,, and in a few weeks time recovered its normal functions after their long impairment. <small> Sigmund Freud, <a name="SFWM2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SFWM2"><cite title="source">&ldquo;From the History of an Infantile Neurosis (The &lsquo;Wolf Man&rsquo;)&rdquo;</cite></a> (1925) 552</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
